{
  "stem": "14060.9",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "So there goes another story how you jump the fence, unbeknown to you.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "Thereafter, I went down to a town called Papa, where my aunt, who is still alive, my father's younger sister, Margit-- her married name was Kohn-- Weiler, maiden name.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "She is the one, with her two children, who were taken out of the ghetto and taken to Budapest from that transport.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "Unfortunately, her husband has not returned, because he was arrested, as I told you earlier.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And I spent two-- a couple of months there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "I have a cousin who is an architect who I took out to Australia and my aunt in 1956, after the revolution, when I already lived in Australia.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "And a sister, who still lives in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And I sort of recuperated there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "I-- we used to go with my cousin to the cellars where they threw all the Jewish books and [INAUDIBLE] and everything and chumashim and mishnayot and everything.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And we literally worked days on end-- as much energy as one had-- to put them together, because nobody really cared.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "And sometime you found your own family's books and all that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "You know, that's the sort of occupation I had.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "And then, nevertheless, after that, I went over to Szombathely, which is very close by, to my uncle's-- my mother's brother-- as we were quite close-- very close, always.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "And, you know, somehow they had no children, and I fitted better into it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "And I was the youngest in the whole community there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "There was practically a 15-year age gap for the next lot of-- no, it wasn't quite.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "But there was a gap.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "Below my age, nobody.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "Don't forget, as I said earlier, in our town I was the only person who survived under the age of 18.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
